# Media System (Core CMS Engine)

The **media table** is the central content registry for the site.

It stores:

- uploaded images
- portfolio media
- logos
- certification logos
- founder image
- other visual assets

Database fields:


id
title
file_url
alt_text
category
placement
description
tech_stack
features
created_at


The `placement` field determines where media appears on the site.

Examples:


home-certification-ticker
about-founder-image
portfolio-grid
logos-page


---

# Media Upload Architecture

Uploads occur in two stages.

### Stage 1 — Blob Upload

Files upload directly to **Vercel Blob Storage**.

Client uses:


@vercel/blob/client


Upload flow:


Client → /api/upload → Vercel Blob → public URL returned


---

### Stage 2 — Metadata Save

After upload, metadata is saved to Neon:


POST /api/media


Fields saved include:

- title
- category
- placement
- description
- tech_stack
- features
- file_url

